HEADWORD: Exergue
<hw>Ex*ergue"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. Gr. <?/ out
+ <?/ work; lit., out work, <it>i. e.</it>, accessory work. See
<er>Work</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Numis.)</fld> <def>The small space beneath
the base line of a subject engraved on a coin or medal. It usually
contains the date, place, engraver's name, etc., or other subsidiary
matter.</def> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

